  "teachingProcess": {
    "message": "Teaching Flow Chart",
    "description": "2.0 index.js"
  },
  "processTips1": {
    "message": "As a cloud-based learning management platform, ULearning is flexible for you to organize your courses using many different teaching/learning models such as flipped classroom, SPOC, blended, hybrid learning, etc.",
    "description": "2.0 index.js"
  },
  "processTips2": {
    "message": "With ULearning, a course can offer multiple classes. The classes can have the shared components as well as individually customized components. They can be taught by an individual teacher or by multiple teachers as a team. The teachers can apply whatever teaching/learning model as needed to the class they are teaching.",
    "description": "2.0 index.js"
  },
  "processTips3": {
    "message": "In the team teaching model, the course managers can add teachers to the team, assign each teacher a class, and set up the privilege for them to teach/manage the course/class. The course managers (only the course managers) can set up, add, and modify the shared course components for all classes in the course. This will greatly reduce the teacher workload of these shared course components across all classes. Teachers in different classes can still have the customized teaching/learning components such assignments, exams, discussions, etc. for their own classes.",
    "description": "2.0 index.js"
  },
  "processTips4": {
    "message": "It is recommended that you choose the appropriate teaching model as desired before the course starts. If the team teaching option is selected, make sure to coordinate to split the tasks among the team members and to avoid any duplicated work. For example, the course just needs to be created once by a team member.",
    "description": "2.0 index.js"
  },
  "processTips5": {
    "message": "The teaching process for both models is listed below. Click each button to see the details of each process step: ",
    "description": "2.0 index.js"
  },
